Neural Networks, Reinforcement Learning. 

Neural Networks: The paper proposes a biologically plausible and minimalistic model of ICx self-organization using a two-dimensional Kohonen map to model the ICx. 

Reinforcement Learning: The model proposed in the paper involves a learn signal based on the owl's visual attention. When the visual attention is focused in the same spatial location as the auditory input, the learn signal is turned on, and the map is allowed to adapt. This is an example of reinforcement learning, where the system receives a signal (in this case, the learn signal) based on its behavior (in this case, the owl's visual attention) to adapt and improve its performance (in this case, the auditory map).
